Measurement Methods Library

This repository contains my personal library of measurement theory, psychometric methods, and applied code developed through coursework, teaching, and research in clinical outcomes.

📚 Purpose
	•	Organize key concepts in measurement (CTT, IRT, factor analysis, validity)
	•	Store reusable R code for psychometric analyses
	•	Provide worked examples for teaching and research
	•	Serve as a reproducible toolkit for PRO and clinical outcomes studies

📁 Structure
	•	concepts/ → Theory notes (e.g., reliability, validity, PCA vs FA)
	•	methods/ → Code for specific techniques (PCA, CFA, IRT, etc.)
	•	workflows/ → End-to-end analyses combining multiple methods
	•	templates/ → Reusable analysis and reporting templates

🧪 Example Use Cases
	•	Running reliability analyses (Cronbach’s alpha, omega)
	•	Conducting exploratory or confirmatory factor analysis
	•	Evaluating construct validity
	•	Analyzing PROMIS and NIH Toolbox data

🛠️ Tools Used
	•	R (tidyverse, lavaan, psych, mirt)
	•	RStudio
	•	SAS
	•	Python

🚧 Status

This is an evolving repository that will grow with new methods, examples, and applications.

📌 Notes

All code is intended for educational and research purposes. Adapt as needed for specific projects.

